#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Shackles "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Yaññasutta "
msgstr "9. Sacrifice "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.76, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.9:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.9:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa mahāyañño paccupaṭṭhito hoti, pañca ca usabhasatāni pañca ca vacchatarasatāni pañca ca vacchatarisatāni pañca ca ajasatāni pañca ca urabbhasatāni thūṇūpanītāni honti yaññatthāya. "
msgstr "Now at that time a big sacrifice had been set up for King Pasenadi of Kosala. Five hundred chief bulls, five hundred bullocks, five hundred heifers, five hundred goats, and five hundred rams had been led to the pillar for the sacrifice. "

msgctxt "sn3.9:1.3"
msgid "Yepissa te honti dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā, tepi daṇḍatajjitā bhayatajjitā assumukhā rudamānā parikammāni karonti. "
msgstr "His bondservants, employees, and workers did their jobs under threat of punishment and danger, weeping with tearful faces. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.173, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.9:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then several mendicants robed up in the morning and, taking their bowls and robes, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

msgctxt "sn3.9:2.2"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then, after the meal, when they returned from alms-round, they went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what was happening. "

msgctxt "sn3.9:2.3"
msgid "“idha, bhante, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa mahāyañño paccupaṭṭhito hoti, pañca ca usabhasatāni pañca ca vacchatarasatāni pañca ca vacchatarisatāni pañca ca ajasatāni pañca ca urabbhasatāni thūṇūpanītāni honti yaññatthāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.9:2.4"
msgid "Yepissa te honti dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā, tepi daṇḍatajjitā bhayatajjitā assumukhā rudamānā parikammāni karontī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn3.9:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn3.9:4.1"
msgid "“Assamedhaṃ purisamedhaṃ, "
msgstr "“Horse sacrifice, human sacrifice, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:4.2"
msgid "sammāpāsaṃ vājapeyyaṃ; "
msgstr "the sacrifices of the ‘stick-casting’, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Niraggaḷaṃ mahārambhā → vājapeyyaṃ niraggaḷaṃ; mahāyaññā mahārambhā (bj, s1-3, km) | vājapeyyaṃ; niraggaḷaṃ mahārambhā (pts1) | vājapeyyaṃ niraggalaṃ mahāyaññā mahārambhā (pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.9:4.3"
msgid "Niraggaḷaṃ mahārambhā, "
msgstr "the ‘royal soma drinking’, and the ‘unbarred’—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:4.4"
msgid "na te honti mahapphalā. "
msgstr "these huge violent sacrifices yield no great fruit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.9:5.1"
msgid "Ajeḷakā ca gāvo ca, "
msgstr "The great sages of good conduct "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:5.2"
msgid "vividhā yattha haññare; "
msgstr "don’t attend sacrifices "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:5.3"
msgid "Na taṃ sammaggatā yaññaṃ, "
msgstr "where goats, sheep, and cattle "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:5.4"
msgid "upayanti mahesino. "
msgstr "and various creatures are killed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.174, sc6
msgctxt "sn3.9:6.1"
msgid "Ye ca yaññā nirārambhā, "
msgstr "But the great sages of good conduct "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:6.2"
msgid "yajanti anukulaṃ sadā; "
msgstr "do attend non-violent sacrifices "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:6.3"
msgid "Ajeḷakā ca gāvo ca, "
msgstr "of regular family tradition, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:6.4"
msgid "vividhā nettha haññare; "
msgstr "where goats, sheep, and cattle, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:6.5"
msgid "Etaṃ sammaggatā yaññaṃ, "
msgstr "and various creatures aren’t killed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:6.6"
msgid "upayanti mahesino. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn3.9:7.1"
msgid "Etaṃ yajetha medhāvī, "
msgstr "A clever person should sacrifice like this, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:7.2"
msgid "eso yañño mahapphalo; "
msgstr "for this sacrifice is very fruitful. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:7.3"
msgid "Etañhi yajamānassa, "
msgstr "For a sponsor of sacrifices like this, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:7.4"
msgid "seyyo hoti na pāpiyo; "
msgstr "things get better, not worse. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:7.5"
msgid "Yañño ca vipulo hoti, "
msgstr "Such a sacrifice is truly abundant, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.9:7.6"
msgid "pasīdanti ca devatā”ti. "
msgstr "and even the deities are pleased.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
